caption: Family and I visited this place for the first time and we will definitely be back. Unique, amazing food for the area, and the staff went out of their way to make it a great experience. Dont pass up the homemade chicken wings and cheese flowers!

Fun and unique experience if you opt for the private chalet - cozy, romantic and good idea for social distancing! Even if I would not plan for a lengthy lounge session on the metal chairs.  The must have fondue was good indeed, but I would have liked more dipping options.  Enthusiastic and courteous staff practicing good social distancing protocol.

I had an awesome breakfast at this place. The staff was wonderful and very friendly. My husband takes care of the Heating and Air Conditioning in the place so it is indeed a comfortable setting there. Delicious food. A must try. I promise you won’t waste your time nor dollars.    Enjoy!

So glad we reserved a chalet as soon as that days reservations became available, and will definitely be going back! It felt safe, reasonably priced, and definitely delicious for brunch! I don't normally get lunch at brunch, but I had to try the duck sandwich and it didn't disappoint.
Nice atmosphere and good cocktails. Wasn't a huge fan of the cuisine though the dishes were still tasty
Interesting experience.
Great restaurant, helpful staff and a awesome cocktail menu. Def try out the raclette experience and visit this H st hot spot ASAP.
Delightful escape of a dining experience. Can't wait to go back.
Great food.... fondu grilled cheese was amazing. Will go back again once the inside is open again.

We visited for early Sunday brunch. The indoor chalet set up was brilliant. We had our own space, kept masks on, had hand sanitizer at the table and the restaurant was not overcrowded.  We had the traditional fondue as well as several other dishes. All were delicious. Our waiter was professional and kind and anticipated our needs.  It was an excellent way to quietly celebrate at birthday during COVID-19 and we appreciate the restaurant's creativity.

Came here last night with a reservation for the “private” chalets. Just to warn other potential patrons who are seeking outdoor dining options during covid - the private chalet is neither private nor outdoors. We felt this was misleading and it seemed other patrons of the chalet felt the same as many were shocked when shown their table.  While the chalets are certainly quaint and cozy, they’re essentially just walls on either side of the table but not in front of the table or closed off on the ceiling. Additionally the tables are inside the restaurant. Perhaps this situation would feel safer with a curtain or door on the front to more completely section off the table from the rest of the restaurant.  Additionally we were disappointed in our service. The server had no knowledge of the drink or wine menu and was unable to advise. Fortunately the manager was able to assist but would say it’s the restaurant’s job to train its staff. We also had to ask multiple times to have our table cleared in order to make space for upcoming dishes.  Wanted to love it, but left underwhelmed. The best part of the evening was the baked goods from their bakery.

what else can a say than just perfect. the. this restaurant does it right. everything they do is done with pride and care. nothing over the top just perfectly executed. i suggest this place to anybody. and btw. did i mention the schnapsicles? i must on your visit.  till next time  thank you for a wonderful time
Food was delicious and our waitress was super kind and nice. I only gave 4 starts bc our table was right under a tree and we had problems with bird poop 🤷

Absolutely amazing!! Their service is delightful, their food is amazing (chicken wings and fondue the best I've had in the city) and their covid precautions were spot on. Thank you Stable for a memorable night out with close friends and such the welcoming and friendly experience. We will be back!
Little Stable outdoor dining was magical! We were offered blankets in case we were cold and bug spray in case of bugs. The fondue was on point!

I love this place. I started coming on the weekends after Covid, and it has quickly become a staple in my weekend routine. The owners are so friendly and welcoming. I am happy to support them and look forward to future visits!

We went to Pier 1354 at Stable and cannot recommend it enough! Delicious food (highly recommend the garlic butter shrimp) and cocktails,  great vibes, and the service was great. They were prepared with hand sanitizer and bug spray - the two must haves for Summer 2020 in DC. We will definitely be back!

(Translated by Google) Great, I heard, recommended by my friends who were there. If I can travel in the fall, I'll go there. Necessarily. See you. Bye  (Original) Ganz toll, habe ich gehört, empfohlen von meinen Freunden die dort waren. Wenn ich am Herbst reisen kann, mach ich ein Abstecher dort hin. Unbedingt. Wir sehen uns. Bye
Great place w wonderful Swiss food. The owners and staff couldn’t be more helpful or nice. Sit at the kitchen bar to watch Chef David work!
What a lovely hidden gem, the food is great and the service delightful.

Amazing ambience and delicious food make for an authentic Swiss experience. The owner was really friendly and kept checking up on us to see everything was going well. The back portion of the restaurant near the bar looks like an Alpine Lodge !! Would definitely visit again when I am in DC.
Food was great. Very homey feeling
Have anything with cheese...you won't regret it.
Good service and good food
This place has great service. The fondue is really good, nice ambiance and good drinks/beer menu. Been there several times and always had a great time. Bit pricey though.
Charming Swiss restaurant. Excellent cheese.  We tried two of the specialties and were pleased.
Try 5he Raclette!
Excellent restaurant in a fun decor.
Great restaurant with delicious food. Excellent service!
Very good food.  Great atmosphere!
Real traditional Swiss Fonduein a  beautiful setting excellent staff
Great drinks & food!
The fondue is really good
Excellent food and atmosphere
Tasty food at a reasonable price, and great service.

I loved the ambiance and decor of this place. The wait staff is friendly and responsive. The French toast was really good. I think it should come with some bacon or meat option. To balance out the sweetness on the plate. I got this hash brown creation that had a fried egg and Gruyere cheese on top of it. It was supposed to have bacon in it. I'm not sure if it did. I didn't taste any. The hash browns were cooked perfectly and I loved the egg and cheese. If it had bacon it needs more cause I completely missed it.  I'm not sure if I would go back but I definitely recommend giving it a try.
What a delightful dinner. Service was incredibly friendly. We tried the fondue, venison, brussel sprouts, Swiss beer and Kirsch. Everything delicious. I loved the design and feel of the restaurant.
Very well decorated. Good food and staff

Outstanding food and atmosphere! My fiance and I came here without a reservation, and there were only spots at the back bar available (so get a reservation!). That being said, the back bar had a great ambiance and the bartender was phenomenal and super friendly. Great European beer/wine/cocktail list as well. The food here was amazing - I had the vol au vent and my fiance had the venison. We also had the flambeed cherry crumble for dessert - so good! Can't recommend this place enough.
Had a great time with friends staff and food was amazing!

I can't say enough good things about Stable- the food, the service, the atmosphere- all are excellent. Silvan helped us plan a surprise brunch for my sister and both the planning and the brunch itself couldn't have gone better. I especially enjoyed the cheese quiche!

Excellent food and service, exceeded my expectations! One note of advice, do not sit at the bar. It's short, very hot from the kitchen and right in the path of everyone walking. Other than that, if you can get a table be sure and sit there. You'll be sure to enjoy your experience!

I was at Stable for a company event with a set menu. It was a pretty setting; the restaurant did a good job of making us feel like we were in a Swiss chalet. The service was just okay. Our CEO asked for a minor change to her plate, and the female server told her, "no substitutions." Seriously? We paid to have the restaurant to ourselves for several hours, and you can't provide a different side dish? I asked a different male server for the SAME minor substitution, and he took care of it, so I know it was possible. Not a lot of attention to our group - no second round of bread, and I had to flag a server down for a soft drink. The food was tasty, but only came out luke warm, although that could have been because they were trying to serve 25 people at the same time. Final word: Good, but not great. Need to work on their service. I wasn't overly impressed, and there are so many other restaurants to try in D.C., I probably wouldn't go back.
Great place for authentic swiss food. My wife is swiss and she says it's like dining at home.

I went here in a larger ground (9 group). We had the Unlimited Raclette Experience,  along with some other appetizers (Brussels sprouts, smoked trout, Italian speck, and chicken liver pate). Honestly, nothing was outstanding. The pate was the best appetizer. All the others were either forgettable or disappointing. In terms of the raclette experience, I don't know if it's because we had such a large group, but it seemed to take forever for our vegetables to cook on the 2 cookers we had at our table (or maybe the server didn't adjust them to a hot enough setting). It made for a frustrating time, just waiting endlessly for the food to cook in front of you. Also, it was really just some potatoes, onions, and cheese on a little grill, so not that exciting or tasty. I wouldn't recommend the Raclette experience as meal, since there's essentially no protein, which is a huge negative, at least in my opinion.
Excellent food. Excellent staff.
Amazing food (try the venison), cool space and great staff.
Great food, outstanding bread and great ambience. Recommend it.
Amazing! The food was incredibly delicious, as were the stories to accompany it. Service was exceptional, and the atmosphere was cozy and warm. Highly recommend this experience.

If cheese is your thing, try the raclette experience with a few friends. It's a unique participatory meal that you won't often find outside of Switzerland. Also unexpectedly excellent bread! A delightful place to brunch.
Everything was 5 star!  I love Zurich style; it is exceptional. I would lick the plate if it wasn’t bad manners. I highly recommend to anyone looking for a great food spot in DC.
Loved the brunch here. There were so many menu items that looked good I have to come back! They also had carafes of mimosa which was nice
Wait staff was knowledgeable. It was hard to get their attention

The music, the staff, the food...everything here was top notch. I stumbled upon this place not knowing what to expect and felt like family as soon as I came in. Every person here made sure my experience was great and the food speaks for itself. A very unique and very worthwhile experience.
Great place for fondue. Heard they have great brunch too!
Authentic Swiss food in D.C.! Try the Absinthe cocktails - fairy tale is my absolute favorite. En Guete!
Nice decor for it's Swiss/American theme. Worth checking out for brunch.
The staff is super nice, the fondues are really good and they have exotic and tasty drinks

I had an awesome experience at Stable DC! The ambiance is amazing, the decor was spot on, very IG worthy. Swiss food is new to me but I'm so happy I got to expand my palate with new flavors and textures. The service was attentive, personable, and most importantly knowledgeable about their food and spirit offering. Lots of great memories made at Stable DC with even more belly laughs! The music was also amazing! To me there's nothing better than a lively seat dance while i eat good food.  Maybe it was the absinthe, maybe it was the food, maybe it was the ambiance... What I know is that I'll be back soon!
I really like the vibe here. The waiters are not pretentious and the drinks were delicious! I definitely will go here again.
We sat at the Chefs Counter and really enjoyed it. Would recommend this place to anyone!
Delicious

Wonderful family-friendly, authentic Swiss fondue-sharing experience!  Additional points for being *in* DC. Next time we'll need to try the raclette option.  Loved the cozy rustic ambiance, and being greeted by one of the [Swiss] owners was a great personable touch.
Delicious food, prompt and polite service. My wife and I have eaten here twice and both times have been excellent across the board.

DC doesn’t have a lot of good German or Swiss restaurants, so I’m really glad this place exists. It’s a busy bustling space with a small-but-mighty menu. We got 1 app, 2 entrees, and 1 dessert: the cheese flowers (100% recommend, my favorite thing we ate), the Stable Rösti (heavy but good), the vol-au-vent (has zero flavor, wouldn’t recommend), and the chocolate praline mousse (amazing!).
The food here is always exceptional. You can have a very good breakfast by rolling in and ordering everything off the sharing menu! Owner and staff are always really friendly and welcoming.

Raclette is a birthday tradition of mine since I was little (I'm French)... loved that I could find a great raclette in Washington DC to keep the tradition alive !! The host is super nice too. Had the best time, I recommend !

I wasn't convinced by the food at this Swiss place.  I'm from France so the food for me here was quite ordinary, particularly given the high price of ~$60/person all told.  So many places to choose from on H, I'd keep going.  This place merits at least $$$, not $$.

This feels to be a very authentic Swiss restaurant, from the vibes of the restaurant when you walk in to the food. They have a ton of drink selections and unique desserts. The service was outstanding and my food was great. I was skeptical at first but it was good.

This place is a hidden gem along H Street. Food is excellent, the wait staff and owner are very friendly. And, you wouldn't expect this from a Swiss restaurant, but I think that their cocktails are among the best I've had in DC -and their bartender has a lot to do with the quality of the execution. Overall, I find myself trying the many different places along H Street, but consistently returning to Stable for a late night snack and cocktail. Give it a try and you won't be sorry.

If you are looking for fresh swizzle cuisine. Stable is the place to go! Their friendly and welcoming staff makes for an amazing visit. I love the decor in the restaurant it reminds me of being home of a farm. it has the look of a true stable. with historic wood and metal interior. Stable offers a number of swizzle dishes. my favorite would be the rachlette dinner, complete with everything you need from a grill to melt the delicious cheese. endless boiled new potatoes, marinated onions and pickled chalets. It is the best cheese that I have ever tasted. they have amazing drinks and the pricing is fair. I mean if you want great quality food, you gonna pay great quality prices. The chef David is a master in the kitchen and you can see for yourself. they have a wonderful kitchen bar seating area that allows you to watch David in his natural state! the General Manager Silvan is a work of art, he is so helpful and very caring about the up keeping of the place, all in all stable gets a 10 in my book! located right in the heart of DC on H street right across from H street country club and right next door from the Vet! stop in and have some amazing food!
We really enjoyed it and look forward to coming back. Everyone was very friendly and the food was really good.

My boyfriend and I have been looking forward to trying Stable for months since moving into the area. Went on a slower Wednesday night so we got our choice of seats- we sat on stools facing the street. Beautiful atmosphere, quick and friendly service, delicious food and amazing drinks. The owner greeted us when we walked in and helped suggest drinks/food. At the end of the meal we ventured to the back of the restaurant- we were shocked by the beautiful "patio" hiding in the far back. Gorgeous bar, high ceilings, beautiful decorations.  All and all- amazing experience. 10/10. We will be back again!!!
The food was just so amazing, and the desert was nothing short of exquisite. Thank you for this memorable experience in my journey to explore the restaurants of DC.
This place is awesome! Food and service was excellent. The owner is from Switzerland and has brought the authentic food from his homeland to ours. Drinks were great too. Can't wait to go back!
Cozy spot with great ambience; romantic spot. Service & food were great! We ordered a lot of items and shared as a table.

My wife, friend, and I went to Stable for a Saturday brunch at 10:30am. It was a holiday weekend and we walked right in without a reservation. By the time we left at noon, there was a healthy flow of people.  Here's what's to love about Stable:  1) Atmosphere: You're transported into Switzerland. The wooden decor, the bread baskets at the bar and the iron spiral staircase in the back dining room, creates atmosphere. The front room has a wall that lifts up in warmer weather giving diners a view of the historic Atlas Theater across the street.  2) Service: Perfect balance of attentive, friendly, and giving you your space to dine with friends.  3) Food: My Stable Casserole was perfect- creamy, balanced, and the fried egg cooked to perfection. My wife loved her cheese plate.  4) Drinks: For just $25, you can make your own mimosa. They bring a big bottle of champagne to your table with a jug of orange juice, and elderflower liquer. It was great!  If you need a solid brunch spot on H Street NE, go here!
Cool atmosphere and tasty food. The drinks were very reasonably priced as well. Busy but not crowded.

My daughter brought me here for Mothers Day Brunch and it was quite good. Swiss precision evident on each plate. I had the Roesti Plate that came with a fried egg and the potatoes were perfect. Of course the bread is excellent and makes a delicious dent in the bakery desert in Capitol Hill. One can buy sweets everywhere but there seems to be no real, from scratch bread makers to be found.  Will go again for an evening meal.

Stable DC is one of the best restaurants in DC. Sylvan the owner is gracious and takes the time to greet each customer. The food is impeccable- you can tell the care and TLC they put into each item in the menu. My only advice- location is mediocre...tough to find parking and the neighborhood can be seedy at times (I might be selfishly saying that as I would to love to have more great restaurants like this closer to MD- like chevy chase, glen echo, friendship heights area). I look forward to seeing this restaurant thrive for many years to come as DC grows and evolves.  I also look forward to Chef David continue pushing the envelope on finding amazing dishes from Switzerland and bringing them here each season and experimenting and innovating yummy food.  ps the chicken liver pate is the best in town.
It's ok !
Great European, Swiss Gemanish Cuisine! The Raclette as a starter was great, the white asparagus with sauce hollandaise amazing! Great service, and typical Swiss digestives!
Incredible food. Extremely friendly staff.

Where else can you find Swiss food in general, let alone Swiss food that enables you to see all 215 dimensional food gates at once?  This food popped my knocker off its rocker so fast I called my long lost cousin and left a voicemail describing my immense pleasure.  These Swiss bubs really got the game figured out, I tell you what.
Great service, great atmosphere, great food, spacious. Best restaurant on H st.
Loved it. Delicious food and attentive service. Everyone was friendly and the atmosphere is warm and welcoming.
Great raclette

Brunch und leckeres Essen! Ausgezeichneter backerei super service Magnifiques pains Silvan Kraemer and Chef David Fritsche have brought a bit of Switzerland to H Street with their now famous ”After my Review” STABLE restaurant. The fresh baked breads are So Good. We met our DC son and his adorable wife Becky here for brunch who have just bought a home down the street. The bread basket and pate were excellent. The eggs were delicious and egg whites perfect! The bacon and sausage were out of this world. Our server was outstanding! Silvan showed us to the beautiful back bar and seating area. They have a pull-up garage for outside seating. Awesome!!!!

We didn't get excited about the main dishes so we ordered four different appetizers - all of them were very good. We also ordered drinks and they were very nice. Way to Joseph was very helpful, so all in all very good experience.
I had the grilled cheese which was delicious. Our server was very nice. The food here is amazing and I would totally recommend it. The restaurant is so cute and has nice decor.

Had an amazing meal here. Our bartender Ian took care of us and was very attentive. The cheese flowers with pear bread were adorable but also delicious!!! Fondue was super tasty, had a great time here, so good.
Friendly place with top notch service and delicious dishes and drinks.

I am surprised I have not written a review yet. But this place is a must. The kitchen is well positioned to create an intimate dinining experience between the customers and the Chefs. The owner, chefs, and waiters/waitresses are some or if not the nicest people I have met. Everyone is friendly. Sunday’s are amazing for brunch and fresh baked bread and donuts. The food is heavenly and just an explosion of taste buds in your mouth. If you are in the District this needs to be your first spot!
Best Swiss fondue this side of the Atlantic. Really surprisingly good.
Great brunch place with a warm and homey interior. The eggs Benedict and muesli were great and the servers were all friendly and attentive.
Hungry? Eat here. Not hungry? Drink here. Then eat.

Stable just takes their service up to the next notch. They take special care in the smallest of details such as folding napkins when you leave the table, helping you put on your coat when you leave, and a manager on site checking in to just be sure that you're enjoying your experience. Our waiter was extremely attentive to our needs and offered excellent recommendations. We went with the capuns, the French Riesling, the belper knolle fondue for two, and the panna cotta. I was honestly embarrassed when I took a bite of the capun and realized I was letting out an audible, "mmmmm." Delicious. the Riesling was a great match for all of the dairy we ate. The fondue was delicious, and provided us with a longer experience, just soaking up the great vibes of this place - watching the chefs prepare dishes, listening in on the German and French conversations around us, and enjoying each other's company. I'll definitely be back to try more of the menu!
Incredible Swiss restaurant amidst a fun and bright decor. Loved the brunch!
Great food. Great staff and owners.  Love the Zurich veal.
Raclette was delicious. Great service. Will definitely come back!
The best swiss food you can get in the US. Great food, great drinks, and a cozy atmosphere.
Excellent taste of Switzerland traditional dishes.  A bit pricy for what you get, but still enjoyed it.   Great for couples.  Not a lot of seating for larger groups.  Reservation recommended.
It was well worth the trip and owner was outstanding work with our student from Switzerland!!
Authentic Swiss food. Nice and friendly wait staff. Beautiful atmosphere. And, at times, you can meet alumni from the university of Zurich.
We enjoyed our fondue dinner last night. It was a delightful meal.

Not too much to say about this place, wasn’t the biggest fan of paying 30 a person for this huge thing of fondue, they need smaller sizes of it, didn’t get an entree, can’t imagine it being much better though
Cozy space, great service, delicious food.  Particular favorites we're the egg dumpling and of course the fondue.
Had the best fondue and raclette ever tasted here by DMV area. I must say even better than some of the restaurants when I was in Switzerland.

Disappointed given the price. This fondue was 30$ per person or 60$ total. Definitely not worth it. It was  bland and the serving size was huge! Why not just charge $30 for half the size? After a bit, it started boiling so they turned off the fire then it got too thick. We ordered the $5 drink with it -- we thought it was an actual drink, and once we got it, thought it was a shot. Finally, the waiter said "it's traditional Swiss drink for dipping the bread, I thought you knew." We were already full when we found out this information. Terrible assumption.
Best Swiss Diner in town! So lovely!
It's a great place!

Authentic Swiss place with charming atmosphere and friendly service. They actually asked us if we wanted our main course right away or wanted to wait after we finished our appetizers. Very thoughtful of them.
It's a cozy, quiet and beautiful place, I enjoyed my time there very much, the food was great and the service was excellent, I'm definitely coming back soon!
Deliciously warming
Amazing food, great atmosphere...you must try the traditional absinthe. I will definitely be heading back in the near future.
Excellent Service, food and atmosphere. Will definitely come back!

Really enjoyed this place. Seems like most of the menu was carb and cheese based, which is okay with me. My boyfriend and I did a date night dinner here and we went knowing nothing about Swiss food (or drinks). Our server was friendly and helpful in walking us through everything. We had a great appetizer and the traditional cheese fondu. All delicious and the atmosphere was fun and laid back. Will definitely come back! Only warning is if you sit at the chef’s table it can get HOT. It was okay with us though on a very cold night!
Great Swiss comfort food. Good service.
Excellent

The food was superb, don’t leave DC without getting the cheese fondue at Stable!! Brussel sprouts were also excellent and service was perfect.  Comforting food, warm and friendly people in a welcoming atmosphere. I will definitely be back to Stable.
Great authentic fondue
Fabulous experience! Excellent authentic fondue and raclette!! Superior staff!!

What a fabulous experience. Wish I had captured more pictures of the space. It was so comfortable and cozy. I didn’t want to leave! The raclette is like a must-do. So. Good. The mains were filling and incredibly delish. Dessert was the perfect way to end the meal - the crème brûlée was beyond. I couldn’t think of a better way to spend a meal.

We had such a wonderful time at this delicious restaurant. The food was interesting and I found it very vegetarian friendly. My 5 year old enjoyed her Berner Rosti and was sad to discover we forgot her leftovers! We were concerned when we walked in and saw the small front room- 5 year olds and small classy rooms can be a challenge!- but the large sunny back room was perfect for our group. All in all a great find in a fun neighborhood!
Great atmosphere, staff and food! Instead of ordering main courses, we ended up ordering all sharables. Highly recommend! And get the brussel sprouts!!
Honestly I have a mixed review about this location and not because the food was not good a just wasn't what I would normally order so I have nothing bad to say about this restaurant
Great food and the staff was very attentive and friendly. The owner was very nice as well. Definitely recommended.
Food was great
Great atmosphere, meals and service!
(Translated by Google) Authentic Swiss cuisine. Everything was really delicious!  (Original) Authentic Swiss cuisine. Alles war echt lecker!
The food was excellently prepared. Got the branzino, chicken and the veal - fresh and delicious. Service was very attentive.
Wonderful place and great service. The staff is really nice and the food is really tasty. Authentic Swiss place.
The best cheese fondue we have had in a very long time!
Get the pot roast. Very nice with just enough starch to complement.
Wow! Such a lovely dining experience. Excellent service, creative menu, and appropriately-priced. The staff cares about good food and it shows.
Fantastic atmosphere! We happened to stop in on Swiss Day. They were eager to help us understand the fare and provided excellent recommendations.
Great Food
Amazing food, served by lovely people. Was a fantastic experience! Beautiful cosy setting for a Sunday brunch with friends
The food is delicious! 90° weather definitely calls for a Schnappsicle...Maribelle and Sparkling Rosé. Will definitely be back.
Cute Swiss themed restaurant with excellent, fresh items

My girlfriend and I had an exquisite experience at Stable for her birthday on Saturday night. We made reservations ahead of time and when we arrived we were seated immediately at a small but very cozy table.  Our waiter couldn't have been better, and was incredibly good at explaining the menu and checking in with us to see if we needed anything.  The food was delicious! I had the Branzino which was cooked perfectly (I was also debating getting the duck) and my girlfriend had the veal. We both had salads as appetizers, and enjoyed the fresh bread. For dessert we had the apple tart.  Everything was truly fantastic and we can't wait to go back again!
What a great spot on H street. Food and drinks are spot on. Nothing fancy but perfectly executed. Highly recommend this place to everybody
Superior service. The best sparking water and Reisling I’ve ever had. Spaghettini was the perfect choice for me!
Incredibly attentive service.

Had dinner here one time and came twice for brunch, really like this place! The food is always super delicious and the service staff is so friendly and accommodating. Defenitly will be back and can only recommend Stable to others!
Wonderful swiss american fare. Open view of the city street while you dine in the summer. Trendy locale that is perfect dor that date for two
Branzino was delish!

We had Easter Brunch with a reservation of 10. From the moment I walked in I was impressed. Very nice place settings, rustic and simple, yet classy. Drinks and appetizers were delicious and when the entree arrived I wasn't sure what to expect since I hadn't eaten at a Swiss Restaurant before, but it was really really good! I ate every bite and left nothing. We also had fondue and creme brulee which was incredible! I can't believe how much I enjoyed myself at a simple brunch. Everyone was smiling and having a great time and nobody wanted to leave. I really want to mention the personal service we received from Silvan and Bartender Extraordinaire Joseph Grimshaw. I will definitely return to this spot. Loved it!

Amazing amazing amazing! My family & I just left their Easter brunch & it was PHENOMENAL! The food was delicious and the service was top notch. They took very good care of us & we even had the pleasure of meeting the owners of this slice of heaven, Silvan & Chef David. The decor & set-up is beyond creative also! You're totally gonna wanna take plenty of pics. Thoroughly enjoyed brunch & just when I thought I couldn't possibly love them anymore....BAM!!!...Allison (our server) came and told us they had Creme Brulee for dessert! My fav! I will definitely be taking my family back to Stable DC! Délicieux!!!
Went for brunch, good drinks and really good food. Our server was very friendly and helpful. The doughnuts were amazing!
Great food and service
Recently enjoyed brunch at Stable. Very god food, specialy the fondue. Service was very good and the owners very personable. I will be back for regular dinner.

This northern European comfort food restaurant is like nothing else in DC, and everything is delicious. The 2 owners are always present (one in the kitchen, the other in the dining room) so the food, service, and artisanal cocktails are consistently spot on. The space is modern but comfortable and quiet enough for pleasant conversation. We'll definitely be back!

They have a nice brunch menu and drinks. Fresh baked breads are new and can be purchased to go. It may look small by the bar but don't be deceived by this cozy area there is plenty of additional seating. I felt like I was in an European restaurant. Enjoy!
Great menu options.  The food was authentic and delicious. The service was superb. Atmosphere is perfect for all occasions.

Had an absolutely wonderful night! Service was terrific, food and drinks were incredible, atmosphere was unique..... I cannot wait to go back! The owner stopped by regularly and was very friendly, which made the night even more special. I'm excited to spread the word about this H Street gem!
Absolutely fantastic!  Every dish was incredibly delicious. The atmosphere was warm and cozy. The staff was extremely attentive and welcoming. I can't wait to return.
Excellent Swiss food.
I'm sure this would be a fantastic find for the Swiss looking for a taste of home, but I cannot get excited by Swiss food

Food is so comforting and never tiring. Drink options are amazing especially for cocktail lovers like me. Atmosphere is perfect to enjoy dinner with friends and family. Staff are amazing and never missed a beat. Until next time

I do not recommend this place based on its customer service.  I walked in here last Saturday ONE hour before closing.  The hostess made a point of stating "We are closing in one hour." I thought to myself..."uhhh okay?" I was a little confused as normally 5-30 minutes is the typical warning, and 30 minutes is stretching it... unless it's a three hour meal kind of place. I then request not to be seated where the draft hits as it was very cold on Saturday.  Guess what?  That's exactly where she decides to seat us.  My friend requested a seat in the back as we saw a room since the initial seating was subject to the draft of cold air from outside. So the hostess seats us at the empty bar. What made this worse was the looks we got from the chef and his sous chef or whatever he was.  IT WAS THE MOST UNWELCOME I HAVE EVER FELT IN A RESTAURANT.  If that was the chef he should be ashamed of himself for his lack of hospitality.  We felt like we were not wanted in the restaurant.  This kind of attitude is the problem in Washington DC restaurants.  When staff think they are too good to serve you and give you an attitude when their entire survival is based on MY MONEY.  Some nerve, I say.  After being received like dirty dish rags we said we were going to another place.  I WILL NEVER GO BACK IN THIS PLACE.  I didn't get to try the food, but if that's the attitude that comes with it, no thank you.  Try acting like that in New York City...you'd be closed in less than six months because no one would put up with that kind of treatment.

I'm Swiss and I absolutely loved it! Truly excellent and authentic food, a very nice atmosphere - traditional and stylish at the same time, great and friendly service. We had the fondue and it's definitely one of the very best I've ever had, and I've had many! :-)

Stable was so much better than I anticipated. I went for Saturday brunch and was sat in their back, well heated courtyard that was quaint as all get out. The food was delicious if not a couple dollars more than it needed to be (my potatoes and eggs were $18). The coffee flowed freely and the Bloody was spicy. I will definitely call ahead next time and do the fondue! I would avoid the breadbasket - it was an unexciting mix of challah, a croissant that was dense instead of flakey, and average county bread.
Very enjoyable Excellent food and service We had brunch for family birthdays

I feel obligated to declare this my all-time time favorite dining experience.  Ever.  The decor is polite, contemporary, but the sort of comfortable kick-back feel where nobody panics over a scuff or two.  Service was awesome, everyone was friendly, but let's get on to the food:  Perfect.  A broth that tasted like liquid meat washing gorgeous melty pork and lovely veg.  Vol-au-vents stuffed with impeccably seasoned chicken and superb Brussels sprouts on the side.  Crazy+yummy chestnut dessert.  On the surface it all looks effortless, but the further you dig in you wish you had room for seconds and realize this place is simultaneously unpretentious and top-class.  A perfect fit for this neighborhood.  Apologies for gushing.  I will return.  With friends.
Great food, cool atmosphere, German-esque food...Perfect spot for dinner.
Delicious meal!
Enjoyed the fondue
Just perfect! 😍
Great food - such fantastic attention to detail - recommend the venison or Pork Belly.  Cheese was fantastic too - real Swiss fusion food

Exotic and decadent menu options. The food was delicious. The service was outstanding. The drink I had was tasty and reasonably priced. They also offer discounts if you show your theatre tickets from Atlas.
Their detail to cocktails is amazing and bar food is better than typically what is expected . The bartenders are personable and the food service is unequivocal.
Great atmosphere and amazing food. Authentic and tasty.
Loved it
Great food, pleasant service. Swiss food! Unexpected surprise on H.
Such great food and service! The Chefs were all very nice too. I had the herb crusted lamb and my wife had the scallops with beef ribs ravioli. It was amazing.

Warm reception, authentic food, attention to detail, and cozy ambiance. The staff was engaging and the quality of everything stood out. Their house-made bread is something else! It will be hard to beat the experience we had here - a real taste of Switzerland. Tschüss!!
Loved the cheese plate and appetizers. Mains were delicious and interesting.
Was here with a group of alums of the University of Zurich. We had the best time. The food was delicious.  We got a tour of the restaurant by Sylvan. A Swiss restaurant was really needed in DC.

Food was good but not really the most amazing Swiss food I have had. In my opinion it was over-priced for what it was. I spend a significant amount of time in Switzerland and didn't really feel anything in this restaurant.  There was way to many staff members for a week night and it felt like they were bored to death. As a result they were hovering a lot and asking every few minutes if all was good. It got annoying after a while. Some where absolutely clueless on the  food itself.  The place is nice but it just does not feel Swiss enough for me. You couldn't really tell from the outside that it was Swiss: that yellow mailbox with the Swiss flag will not be enough for most customers in the area to guess the theme.  Overall, I wish this place would be more Swiss in the decor and the food and really give me the experience I was expecting. I hope it works as it would be a great addition to H Street and grows into what it has the potential to be.

This was comfort food at its best. The ambiance is open in the front and very cozy in the back. The service was prompt and very friendly. The ramp spätzle was to die for and the bread made in house was fantastic. We look forward to trying the Raclette Dinner experience with friends.
Great experience and amazing restaurant!
